
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee {
  + hasOscar: boolean
}

class Director extends CreativeEmployee {
  + assistantName: String
}

class Actor extends CreativeEmployee {
  + educationCompleted: String
}

class Technician extends Employee {
  + fieldOfActivity: String
}

class FilmSet {
  + location: String
}

class Film {
  + title: String
  + releaseYear: int
  + genre: String (Thriller, Action, Horror, Comedy)
}

class Screenwriter {
  + name: String
  + mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  + title: String
  + version: String
  + date: Date
  + numberOfScenes: int
  + plot: String
  + sourceType: String (Novel, Concept)
}

class Novel {
  + title: String
  + author: String
}

' Define associations and relationships

' Employee types
Employee <|-- CreativeEmployee
CreativeEmployee <|-- Director
CreativeEmployee <|-- Actor
Employee <|-- Technician

' FilmSet and Film relationship (many-to-many)
FilmSet "0..*" --> "0.." Film : usedIn
Film "0.." --> "0..*" FilmSet : shotAt

' Screenwriter writes screenplays (1 to many)
Screenwriter "1" --> "0.." Screenplay : writes

' Screenplay is based on either a novel or concept (generalization)
Screenplay <|-- NovelBasedScreenplay
Screenplay <|-- ConceptBasedScreenplay
NovelBasedScreenplay --> "1" Novel : basedOn
ConceptBasedScreenplay --> "1" Concept : basedOn

' Film is based on a screenplay (1 to 1)
Film "1" --> "1" Screenplay : basedOn

' Actors read screenplays (many-to-many)
Actor "0.." --> "0.." Screenplay : reads

' Directors implement screenplays (many-to-one)
Director "0.." --> "1" Screenplay : implements

@enduml

---

### Notes:
- The `Screenplay` class has two specializations: `NovelBasedScreenplay` and `ConceptBasedScreenplay`, which are not explicitly named in your text but are implied by the description.
- A **film** is associated with exactly one **screenplay**, and each **screenplay** is written for exactly one **film**.
- A **screenwriter** can write multiple screenplays.
- **Actors** must **read** screenplays for their roles.
- **Directors** implement the screenplay.
- **FilmSet** and **Film** have a many-to-many relationship since a film set can be used for multiple films, and a film can be shot at multiple sets.

